[DES-2] Description of Files
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Here is a listing of all files associated with Recitation 5 and what their
purpose is:

                    .../README                  - Current document 
                    .../recitation5.pdf         - Provided slides/reference
                    .../src/quicksort.py        - Quicksort example code
                    .../src/webapp.py           - Webapp example code
                    .../src/recitation5.odp     - OpenOffice recitation4 source
                    .../src/wiki_quick.png      - Quicksort Wikipedia Screen




[RUN-3] How to Run
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

You may directly execute the Python scripts.  When running webapp.py, it will
start a web server running locally.  You need to first install Flask.  You can
do this by using Python's 'easy_install flask'.  Go to this URL to see results:

                    http://localhost:5000

It defaults to port 5000.

For trying out the quicksort.py script, you may also just run it directly.  You
can see the doctest module in action with this command:

                    python quicksort.py -v
